33 years of following my wildest dreams… 🥂🎂🧚🏽‍♂️

Motherhood has been the best gift I’ve ever received. Raising my children and teaching them how to survive in this world, all while keeping a smile hasn’t been the easiest task. However, I wake up everyday ready for the challenge because they deserve just that. I am so happy to hear “Mommy, Mommy!!” Lol it’s so soothing. Cheers to these throwbacks lol 🥂🥹💐🌷 unedited raw random photos 🫶🏽

We have to do better as people to keep our communities safe and clean. I’m asking that if it’s in your heart please come out to my first @themckenzieproject event. I’ve been working on my non for profit for a while now trying to figure out where to start. I finally chose to start with spring cleaning at my neighborhood park! There’s so much trash to be picked up so the children can run through the sprinklers and enjoy themselves. Meet me there at the kids area and follow us @themckenzieproject 🫶🏽

Time to sprinkle some fairy dust in the Bronx 🧚🏽

Let’s all come together and make an effort to do the right thing. Echo Park in the Bronx needs lots of TLC, and being that it’s a neighborhood park it’s our responsibility to keep it clean. I hope to see you there 🫶🏽

Join us every Saturday from 9am-11am in helping to make #acleanerbronx 🌱
Our first cleanup was a success and we ask that you join our journey as we prepare for the Echo Park Community Garden by @themckenzieproject 🫶🏽

For a long time I questioned what I would leave behind for my children. The most impactful thing I could think about is leaving them land. For so many years I never knew where I wanted to purchase. I was so scared and nervous. Finally, I came across an opportunity that I couldn’t pass, so I purchased 7.5 acres with my husband in the Catskills, NY. 1hr and 30 mins from NYC.  @90eastvineyards is more than a dream. It might not be complete overnight but we will definitely start with this. 🙏🏽🦋☀️ @lamelazitareyes

From a young age my Godfather (Uncle Greg) took me to explore and develop a deep love for the theatre. I would take the train out to the city from Long Island as a young girl and have the most elaborate experiences with him exploring the city and seeing the most iconic Broadway shows. At 33, we still do this and it brings us both so much joy. Cheers to Uncle Greg for being nothing short of amazing. From my second day in this world to 33 years later, you are still in my life exposing me to nothing but the best honey 😍💕🫶🏽

Respect your SPIRIT enough to constantly create environments that keep you peaceful and calm 💕 That’s where the true beauty is. It matters more what you have in the inside. Don’t become lost because the culture keeps changing. Stay consistent and respect yourself ⭐️

Create something that makes you happy. I went with Rosé 💫
